solutions.content:
It's more efficient to go right-to-left; we just need to fix the sign in the end.
## Right-to-Left
**C++**
```cpp
int alternateDigitSum(int n) {
    int res = 0, sign = 1;
    for (; n; n /= 10) {
        sign *= -1;
        res += sign * n % 10;
    }
    return sign * res;
}
```
## Left-to-Right
This requires a string conversion, adding O(log n) memory complexity.
**C++**
```cpp
int alternateDigitSum(int n) {
    auto s = to_string(n);
    int res = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); ++i)
        res += (i % 2 ? -1 : 1) * (s[i] - '0');
    return res;
}
```

