# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
1) Reverse the Number.
2) Assign a flag as false , sum as the MSB .
3) Iterate the rev until the number is zero:
    i) If flag is true ,add the digit value to the sum.
    ii) If flag is false , subract the digit value to the sum.
    iii) Reverse the flag.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Firstly revese the number , set a flag as false,sum as the MSB. Travers the each digit of the number ,for each iteration reverse the flag ; if the flag is true add the digit value to the sum ;else subract the didit value to the sum.
Return the sum value!

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(m),
where m is the length of the number.

- Space complexity: O(1).

<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
# Code
```
class Solution
{
    public int alternateDigitSum(int n)
    {
        boolean flag = false;
        int rev = 0;
        while (n > 0)
        {
