<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
we are asked to calculate sum of digits with alternate + and - sign. if we carefully observe, we see at even index we have + and at odd index we have -. **so we will use the number as an array without  declaring array.**

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. first of all, we have to extracts digits from n one by one. we starts extracting from beginning.
2. for that, set count = 1 and multiply it by 10 untill n becomes 0. count will have zero's equal to number of digits in num.
---
**for example** -  
1. **num = 521. count will be 1000.**
2. **num = 40 , count = 100.
 but still we can extract n's first digit. for that simply divide count by 10.**
---
3. run a loop from i =0 till n > 0.
4. if i is even add the digit to sum else subtract it.

