# Intuition
This was a simple math, where first I had to convert it to a digit list. While converting I could get the digits in reverse so I stored in Stack and then pop each digit and add or subtract it according to the alternate variable.

# Approach
Used Stack to store the digits in reverse, and pop it as it will come out in correct order.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n) where n is the number of digits in the number.

- Space complexity:
O(n) as we are storing the digits in a Stack.

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int alternateDigitSum(int n) {
        var digits = getDigits(n);

        int alternate = 0;
        int sum = 0;
        while (!digits.isEmpty()) {
            if (alternate % 2 == 0)
                sum += digits.pop();
            else
                sum -= digits.pop();

            alternate++;
        }

        return sum;
    }

    private static Stack<Integer> getDigits(int n) {
        var digits = new Stack<Integer>();
        while(n > 0) {
            digits.push(n % 10);
            n /= 10;
        }

        return digits;
    }
}
```

